  "text": "Scaffold implantation process represents a \"doubleedged sword\"; the struts should be embedded well enough to prevent flow separation due to the protruded obstacles in the new constituted vessel surface. There is however an increased risk of vessel wall stretch and injury in case of deep embedment [CITATION_1] . The balance should be respected meticulously during the implantation process to avoid from both vessel wall injury and increment in flow disruption.",
